uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.model.data.forms

Interface RoleSelector<B extends DataObject>

  • Type Parameters:
    B - Type of object relationship is for.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractRelationship, PersonRelationship, Relationship
    Deprecated.

    @Deprecated
public interface RoleSelector<B extends DataObject>
    Like Selector this interface means the implementing class can provide Form Inputs. In this case the Input is customised for the AppUser requesting the form. Available selections may be restricted to those where the AppUser has a specified role with respect to the target objects. How this role is defined is implementation specific. This is deprecated in favour of querying relationships directly but is still in use.
    Author:
    spb
    See Also:
    Selector
